items.name: Wuthering Nights (BOTC Script) – Ryan Faries - Intermediate
items.description: Wuthering Nights is a custom BOTC script by Zwischenzugger that features many powerful townsfolk (Chambermaid, Innkeeper, Philosopher, Magician, etc) while also features some powerful Demons and Minions (Goblin, Spy, Fang Gu, etc).

We have really strong trans and nonbinary, representation in the Clocktower community, and I think it’d be really nice to get to build on that and get to know folks a bit more. My idea for this is to provide a space for trans* (binary or nonbinary) people in the clocktower community could hang out and get to know each other, socializing and building community.

items.name: Whose Cult is it Anyway?
items.description: It’s up to either team to decide whether to trust the Cult, or undermine it! Good townsfolk have powerful abilities to check on alignment. The Cult Leader can win easily, if trusted. Outsiders are either hiding their true role, being forced to bluff. Evil players will pay close attention to the wild accusations of the town and hope the *wrong* players are executed! The Demons have a range of options to escape, or sew wild misinformation.

items.description: There are now, what, 6000 scripts?  Remember when there were only 3?  Remember when you were only good at 1 of them?  Remember when you thought the Spy was OP?  Remember when you thought the Butler was awful?  Let's revisit those times.  And let's revisit those times through the eyes of someone going through those stages as this game will be Storytold by a father/daughter team.  She's 13 years old, so expect a lot of dad jokes and embarrassment.

items.name: Ben Special Guest ST Game
Killing with Kindness: Ethics and inclusivity in BoTC
items.description: Blood on the Clocktower is a game of deceit and lies. It's fun to get away with hiding the truth and carrying your team to victory. But every game ends, and we need to be sure that the folks we've betrayed will be willing to play with us again after we rerack. Join sincerity in a discussion of equity in our playstyles, staying aware of nonverbal signals, and remembering to make space for the quieter players among us.

items.name: Sheriff of Nottingham
items.description: As a merchant, you want to make as much profit as you can with your goods, but first you'll have to get past the notorious Sheriff of Nottingham. A game of Bluffing, Bribery and Smuggling!
items.long_description:
Players, in the role of merchants, see this as an opportunity to make quick profits by selling goods in the bustling city during the Prince's visit. However, players must first get their goods through the city gate, which is under the watch of the Sheriff of Nottingham. Should you play it safe with legal goods and make a profit, or risk it all by sneaking in illicit goods? Be mindful, though, as the Sheriff always has his eyes out for liars and tricksters and if he catches one, he very well may confiscate those goods for himself!

In Sheriff of Nottingham, players will not only be able to experience Nottingham as a merchant of the city, but each turn one player will step into the shoes of the Sheriff himself. Players declare goods they wish to bring into the city, goods that are secretly stored in their burlap sack. The Sheriff must then determine who gets into the city with their goods, who gets inspected, and who may have their goods confiscated!

Do you have what it takes to be seen as an honest merchant? Will you make a deal with the Sheriff to let you in? Or will you persuade the Sheriff to target another player while you quietly slip by the gate? Declare your goods, negotiate deals, and be on the lookout for the Sheriff of Nottingham!

items.name: The Thing: The Board Game
items.description: From BGG: The Thing is a game that mixes different mechanisms to create an experience that is as faithful as possible to that of the original film. It is a "hidden role" game, in which one player is initially the Thing and the others players are humans. The purpose of the Thing is to infect others, to prevent the survivors from escaping from the base (which can happen three different ways), or to try to escape with them by behaving as a human.
